{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013X5qHrzLXbVutLmLeZWcY4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The pods 0 and 1 are the old ones (age 8m48s and 8m47s), but they haven't been restarted. And crdb-cluster-2 is the new one (age 4m12s). The issue is:\n\n1. The old pods (0 and 1) still show HTTP probes (not HTTPS) in their describe output - these are old pods\n2. crdb-cluster-2 is running with the new config but its readiness probe is failing with HTTP 503\n\nWait, crdb-cluster-0 shows age 8m48s - that's the original age from when pods were first created (115s in the first check). \n\nSince StatefulSet restarts from the highest ordinal downward, crdb-cluster-2 got restarted first and is now Running but failing its readiness probe with a 503 error. The problem might be that CockroachDB is in secure mode but the cluster initialization hasn't completed properly.\n\nI'm checking the certificate file permissions—the defaultMode of 256 (octal 0400) should work for the key files since we're running as root. But there's a deeper issue: the cluster is currently in insecure mode with existing data, and we need to handle the transition to secure mode carefully.\n\nThe 503 readiness probe failure suggests the pod started in secure mode while the other nodes are still in insecure mode, which prevents cluster quorum. CockroachDB doesn't support live migration between modes—we'd need to restart all nodes simultaneously to transition the entire cluster.\n\nLet me check the logs from crdb-cluster-2 to understand what's actually happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":880,"cache_read_input_tokens":38216,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":880},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_manage