{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016bPk3QtDdStDgBXcd77Yss","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The node certs are mounted (`ca.crt`, `node.crt`, `node.key`). But to run `cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`, it also needs `client.root.crt` and `client.root.key` in that directory. Currently only the node certs are there.\n\nI need to also put the client certs in the same directory. I have a few options:\n1. Create a combined secret with all certs (node + client) and mount it\n2. Copy client certs from a separate location\n3. Temporarily write client certs to the pod's filesystem\n4. Mount the client certs secret to the same directory\n\nThe client certs are already in the `crdb-client-root-certs` secret, but I can't write directly to the mounted `/cockroach/cockroach-certs` directory since it's read-only from the secret mount. I need to either mount both secrets to the same location or use an init container to combine them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":489,"cache_read_input_tokens":48930,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":489},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3dab9157-8ef2-439e-889f-81c8fe8a1144","uuid":"2173ed9c-2782-46ed-bc04-38056086a271","request_id":"req_011CcLB9g3RkGC1PbDff28tH"}
